## Java API (Companion Plugin)

### Adding as Dependency

#### Maven
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.geysermenu</groupId>
    <artifactId>companion-api</artifactId>
    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <scope>provided</scope>
</dependency>
```

#### Gradle
```kotlin
compileOnly("com.geysermenu:companion-api:1.0.0-SNAPSHOT")
```

### Basic Usage

```java
import com.geysermenu.companion.api.GeyserMenuAPI;
import com.geysermenu.companion.api.MenuButton;
import com.geysermenu.companion.api.FormBuilder;

public class MyPlugin extends JavaPlugin {
    
    @Override
    public void onEnable() {
        // Get the API instance
        GeyserMenuAPI api = GeyserMenuAPI.getInstance();
        
        // Register a global menu button (appears for all players)
        api.registerButton(MenuButton.builder()
            .id("my-plugin-button")
            .text("My Plugin Menu")
            .imageUrl("https://example.com/icon.png")
            .priority(10)  // Lower = higher in list
            .onClick((player, session) -> {
                // Handle button click
                player.sendMessage("You clicked my button!");
                
                // Open a sub-menu
                sendMyPluginMenu(player);
            })
            .build());
    }
    
    private void sendMyPluginMenu(Player player) {
        GeyserMenuAPI api = GeyserMenuAPI.getInstance();
        
        // Create a simple form
        api.sendForm(player, FormBuilder.simple()
            .title("My Plugin Menu")
            .content("Select an option:")
            .button("Option 1", () -> {
                player.sendMessage("You selected option 1!");
            })
            .button("Option 2", "textures/items/diamond", () -> {
                player.sendMessage("You selected option 2!");
            })
            .onClose(() -> {
                player.sendMessage("Menu closed");
            })
            .build());
    }
    
    @Override
    public void onDisable() {
        // Unregister your buttons
        GeyserMenuAPI.getInstance().unregisterButton("my-plugin-button");
    }
}
```

### Registering Conditional Buttons

```java
// Button only visible to players with permission
api.registerButton(MenuButton.builder()
    .id("admin-button")
    .text("Admin Panel")
    .condition(player -> player.hasPermission("myplugin.admin"))
    .onClick((player, session) -> {
        openAdminPanel(player);
    })
    .build());

// Button only visible to Bedrock players in a specific world
api.registerButton(MenuButton.builder()
    .id("world-specific")
    .text("World Menu")
    .condition(player -> player.getWorld().getName().equals("lobby"))
    .onClick((player, session) -> {
        // Handle click
    })
    .build());
```

### Sending Modal Forms

```java
api.sendForm(player, FormBuilder.modal()
    .title("Confirm Action")
    .content("Are you sure you want to do this?")
    .button1("Yes, do it!")
    .button2("No, cancel")
    .onConfirm(() -> {
        player.sendMessage("Action confirmed!");
        performAction(player);
    })
    .onDeny(() -> {
        player.sendMessage("Action cancelled.");
    })
    .build());
```

### Listening for Player Events

```java
api.onPlayerJoin(playerData -> {
    getLogger().info("Bedrock player joined: " + playerData.getName());
    getLogger().info("UUID: " + playerData.getUuid());
    getLogger().info("XUID: " + playerData.getXuid());
});

api.onPlayerLeave(playerData -> {
    getLogger().info("Bedrock player left: " + playerData.getName());
});
```

### Getting Online Bedrock Players

```java
List<BedrockPlayer> bedrockPlayers = api.getOnlineBedrockPlayers();

for (BedrockPlayer bp : bedrockPlayers) {
    getLogger().info("Player: " + bp.getName() + " (UUID: " + bp.getUuid() + ")");
}
```

